      • formatEta

        public static java.lang.String formatEta(float n)
        Formats a duration into a scale-dependent expression. For example, a duration of 50 seconds will be shown as "50 seconds", while a duration of 2000 seconds will be shown as "18 minutes" (exact seconds not shown).
        Parameters:
        n - The duration (in seconds)
        Returns:
        The formatted expression
